{{Expand Spanish|date=February 2018}} {{Infobox monument | name = Monument to the fallen in the Falklands | native_name = Monumento a los caídos en Malvinas | native_name_lang = es | country = | image = Monumento Caidos Malvinas.jpg
| image_size = 300px | caption = Monumento a los caídos en Malvinas, in the [[Plaza San Martín (Buenos Aires)|Plaza San Martín]]. | dedicated_to = Argentine soldiers killed in [[Falklands War]] | map_image = Argentina Buenos Aires City | map_text = Location in Buenos Aires City | open = {{start date|1990|06|24}} | coordinates = {{coord|34|35|38.2|S|58|22|30.3|W||display=inline}} | location = [[Avenida del Libertador]], [[San Martín, Buenos Aires|San Martín]], [[Buenos Aires]], [[Argentina]] | designer = Andrés Morán }}
The '''Monumento a los caídos en Malvinas''' ({{lang-en|Monument to the Fallen in the Falklands}}) is a [[cenotaph]] in [[Plaza San Martín (Buenos Aires)|Plaza San Martín]], in [[Buenos Aires]], dedicated to the 649 Argentine soldiers who were killed in the [[Falklands War]]. The inscription reads ''La nación también rinde homenaje a los que guardan en su cuerpo o memoria las huellas del combate''. (''The nation honors also those who keep traces of the struggle on their bodies or in their memories''.)
